Question: What is Express.js?
Express.js is a minimal, fast, and flexible web framework for Node.js used to build web applications and RESTful APIs. It simplifies server-side development 
by providing features like routing, middleware, requestâ€“response handling, and error management on top of Node.js.

Key Points to Mention:
Built on Node.js
Uses middleware to process requests
Supports routing for different HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
Ideal for REST APIs and backend services
Lightweight and highly extensible

One-line Answer (Quick):
Express.js is a lightweight Node.js framework that simplifies building web servers and REST APIs.



What is an API?
API (Application Programming Interface) is a set of rules and endpoints that allows two software applications to communicate with each other.

One-line interview answer â­
An API allows different applications to communicate by sending requests and receiving responses.

Why APIs are Used?
To enable communication between client and server
To share data and functionality
To build scalable and modular applications
To allow frontend and backend to work independently

Real-World Analogy
ğŸ‘‰ Restaurant Example
You (Client) â†’ place order
Waiter (API) â†’ takes request
Kitchen (Server) â†’ prepares food
Waiter (API) â†’ delivers response
You never enter the kitchen â€” same way client never accesses server logic directly.



2ï¸âƒ£ REST API (Very Important â­â­â­)
REST (Representational State Transfer) is an architectural style for designing APIs using HTTP methods.

Common HTTP Methods:
| Method | Purpose        |
| ------ | -------------- |
| GET    | Fetch data     |
| POST   | Create data    |
| PUT    | Update data    |
| PATCH  | Partial update |
| DELETE | Remove data    |


API Requestâ€“Response Cycle => 
Client sends request
Server processes request
Server sends response (JSON/XML)
Client consumes response




API Status Codes (Very Important)
| Code | Meaning      |
| ---- | ------------ |
| 200  | OK           |
| 201  | Created      |
| 400  | Bad Request  |
| 401  | Unauthorized |
| 403  | Forbidden    |
| 404  | Not Found    |
| 500  | Server Error |

One-Minute Interview Answer â­
An API is a communication interface that allows applications to exchange data. In web development, APIs commonly use HTTP methods like GET and POST
to perform CRUD operations, following REST principles and returning data in JSON format.


What is a REST API?
REST API (Representational State Transfer API) is a web API that follows REST architectural principles and uses HTTP methods to perform operations on resources.

One-line interview answer â­
A REST API allows clients to interact with server resources using standard HTTP methods in a stateless way.


REST API Example (Express.js)
app.get('/users', (req, res) => {
  res.status(200).json({ message: "Users fetched" });
});

app.post('/users', (req, res) => {
  res.status(201).json({ message: "User created" });
});


â“ Which data format is used?
ğŸ‘‰ Mostly JSON, sometimes XML.

â“ Why REST API is popular?
ğŸ‘‰ Simple, scalable, lightweight, works well with HTTP.

One-Minute Interview Answer â­
A REST API is an architectural style for building web services that uses HTTP methods to perform CRUD operations on resources. 
It is stateless, scalable, and commonly returns JSON responses.


Question: Why Express.js?
Express.js is used because it simplifies building web servers and REST APIs in Node.js by providing features like routing, middleware, 
and easier requestâ€“response handling, while remaining fast and lightweight.


